721687f-b.title: Manhattan: Monroe Street - Gouverneur Street
721687f-b.text:
Monroe Street, east across Gouverneur Street, showing
the demolition for the government sponsered public housing
project, the USHA ''Vladeck Houses''. The cleared block-
front in the fofeground is the narrow frontage from Gouver-
neur to Scammel Street's.
June 23, 1939
No's. 1-2-3
P. L. SPERR
NO REPRODUCTIONS

721690f-a.title: Manhattan: Monroe Street - Gouverneur Street
721690f-a.text:
Monroe Street, north side, east across Gouverneur
Street, showing the site of the future USHA ''Vladeck
Houses'' during demolition. The cleared block front
in the center is the narrow Gouverneur to Scammel
Street frontege. In the background appears the cables
of the Williamsburg Bridge.
June 24, 1939
P. L. sPERR
NO REPRODUCTIONS
